    <title>midata impact assessment: order making power for midata</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary></summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assesses the impact of proposals to set up a power to make the midata programme compulsory. Government has a role in ensuring all relevant firms in a sector release information on a consistent basis. Government intervention would only require firms to release data, on request, if they already collect it. This aims to give consumers access to their transaction data to make better informed decisions and choose products which offer them the best value. This in turn will reward firms offering the best value. Relates to the midata consultation URN 12/943, and the government response 12/1283.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
